arch:property.oc:show_val: Flot 2904 - sample 2 - diagnostics only Also flot 2907 - sample 3 - > 4mm diagnostics recorded. And sample 4, no 2906 same. A spit from the midden deposit in Space 181. A medium-size unit, generally light to medium brown, not very weathered with a small amount of burning. Element representation is overwhelmingly long bone fragments, with some teeth and toes and virtually no axial skeleton. Taxa are largely sheep/goat size with some 05 and 07. There is almost no digested or chewed bone, fragmentation is fairly large. Maybe more staining than 4836? November 2000: more material arrived - misidentified as stone. All from Sample 3, mostly flot frags, except for three O/C sesamoid bones. No burning, slight weathering. [sm] Last Number = 445

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
